title: Google\Cloud\BigQuery\Migration\V2\MigrationSubtask
name: MigrationSubtask
description:
A subtask for a migration which carries details about the configuration of the subtask. The content of the details should not matter to the end user, but is a contract between the subtask creator and subtask worker.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.bigquery.migration.v2.MigrationSubtask

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. Immutable. The resource name for the migration subtask. The ID is server-generated. Example: projects/123/locations/us/workflows/345/subtasks/678

params.name: data.task_id
params.description: The unique ID of the task to which this subtask belongs.

params.name: data.type
params.description: The type of the Subtask. The migration service does not check whether this is a known type. It is up to the task creator (i.e. orchestrator or worker) to ensure it only creates subtasks for which there are compatible workers polling for Subtasks.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Output only. The current state of the subtask.

params.name: data.processing_error
params.description: Output only. An explanation that may be populated when the task is in FAILED state.

params.name: data.resource_error_details
params.description: Output only. Provides details to errors and issues encountered while processing the subtask. Presence of error details does not mean that the subtask failed.

params.name: data.resource_error_count
params.description: The number or resources with errors. Note: This is not the total number of errors as each resource can have more than one error. This is used to indicate truncation by having a resource_error_count that is higher than the size of resource_error_details.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: Time when the subtask was created.

params.name: data.last_update_time
params.description: Time when the subtask was last updated.

params.name: data.metrics
params.description: The metrics for the subtask.
